.TH "sw_cfg" 9 "sw_cfg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sw_cfg \- set switch register bits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" sw_cfg
.BI "(struct ksz_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u32 addr "  ","
.BI "u16 bits "  ","
.BI "int set "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
The hardware instance.
.IP "addr" 12
The address of the switch register.
.IP "bits" 12
The data bits to set.
.IP "set" 12
The flag indicating whether the bits are to be set or not.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function sets or resets the specified bits of the switch register.
